{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","data":{"body":"CALIBRATION-3 ADJUDICATION (AC2). Decision rule as pre-registered in this ticket's plan; replay rows cited as (n, validity, rev_rr, p90, fire). Headline: under plan-v2, NO criterion reaches BLOCK-ELIGIBLE (the rule needs rev_rr>=0.6 + validity>=0.55 + indet<=0.15; best rev_rr in the whole corpus is G5 at 0.565). Second headline: p90 surviving priority is EXACTLY 0.85 for nearly every criterion - the hard-override floor's signature saturating the priority distribution (see the floor-attribution comment on story 7d91 / large-sleepful-needlefish).\n\nPer-criterion decisions for the 11 currently-blocking criteria:\n- T5e (thr 0.60): replay row (901, 0.391, 0.21, 0.27, 0.72) -> class FP-PRONE (validity 0.391 < 0.45; verifier drops 59% of its findings). Rule (b): DEMOTE to advisory (chosen over raise-to-0.90 because its surviving p90 priority is 0.27 - a 0.90 threshold is a de facto demotion that still pays block-path cost and misrepresents posture; demotion keeps the coaching signal). APPLIED in criteria_routing.json.\n- T8 (0.70): (2715, 0.595, 0.208, 0.85, 0.76) -> ADVISORY-KEEP class; rule (d): KEEP 0.70. Borderline recorded: highest-volume criterion; worst subq impact_follows_necessarily no-rate 0.72.\n- G1G2 (0.70): (2263, 0.614, 0.214, 0.85, 0.95) -> KEEP 0.70. Fire-rate 0.95 (fires on nearly every review it runs in).\n- G6 (0.60): (2123, 0.581, 0.213, 0.85, 0.94) -> KEEP 0.60. Same saturation pattern.\n- E4 (0.75): (1659, 0.618, 0.276, 0.85, 0.82) -> KEEP 0.75.\n- E2 (0.60): (1446, 0.524, 0.263, 0.80, 0.82) -> KEEP 0.60. Validity 0.524 is the weakest of the keepers; watch in calibration 4.\n- T1 (0.70): (1283, 0.554, 0.281, 0.85, 0.71) -> KEEP 0.70.\n- F1 (0.60): (912, 0.555, 0.354, 0.85, 0.65) -> KEEP 0.60. p75 is ALSO 0.85 (floor saturation strongest here).\n- COH (0.60): (557, 0.576, 0.404, 0.75, 0.47) -> KEEP 0.60. Best rev_rr among keepers (0.404).\n- T4 (0.70): (449, 0.474, 0.323, 0.57, 0.40) -> KEEP 0.70. Validity 0.474 sits 0.024 above the FP-PRONE line; explicitly flagged for calibration 4.\n- G5 (0.60): (97, 0.469, 0.565, 0.53, 0.09) -> KEEP 0.60. Highest rev_rr in corpus (0.565, nearly BLOCK-ELIGIBLE) but validity 0.469 borderline and n=97 modest.\n\nNon-blocking criteria: no promotions (nothing is BLOCK-ELIGIBLE). T7/F4/ISF are FP-PRONE but already advisory - no action. T5d n=17 LOW-DATA -> KEEP advisory (rule a).\n\nINTERPRETATION CAUTION recorded for calibration 4: rev_rr (criterion-load drop across material revisions) is structurally depressed in BLOCK-loop regimes with serialized discovery (87% of blocking findings are new each round - d195 evidence), so the uniform ADVISORY-KEEP outcome should NOT be read as 'demote everything'; it says the discriminating signal under plan-v2 is NOT the per-criterion threshold but the hard-override floor (35.5% of all blocks are floor-driven). The structural lever is the floor split (story 7d91), not further threshold surgery. NET RESULT: one change (T5e demoted), ten keeps, all recorded in docs/experiments/plan-review-threshold-calibration.md 'Calibration 3' section landed with this ticket's Gerrit change."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1784141192664389001,"uuid":"ff73ca28-8f4e-4240-a727-f03186902560"}